Yes вАФ **you can use `async/await` inside `useEffect`**, **but not directly on the effect callback itself**.  
This is a **very common React interview question**, so letвАЩs explain it cleanly вЬЕ

***

## вЬЕ Short InterviewвАСReady Answer

> You cannot make the `useEffect` callback `async`, but you can define and call an async function **inside** `useEffect`.

