## вЬЕ Handling Errors with `async/await` in `useEffect`

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  const fetchData = async () => {
    try {
      const res = await fetch("/api/data");
      const data = await res.json();
      setData(data);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error(error);
    }
  };

  fetchData();
}, []);
```

вЬЕ Always wrap async logic in `try/catch`  
вЬЕ Prevents unhandled promise rejections

