## вЬЕ OneвАСLine Interview Answer

> You cannot make `useEffect` itself async, but you can call an async function inside it to use async/await safely.

***

## вЬЕ 10вАСSecond Interview Explanation

> Since `useEffect` expects a cleanup function, its callback cannot be async, but we can define and invoke an async function inside the effect for data fetching.

